LenÃ§Ã³is Maranhenses is located in northeastern Brazil, this unique national park unveils a mesmerizing landscape that seems like a blend of dreams and reality. Vast expanses of pristine, white sand dunes stretch as far as the eye can see, interrupted only by crystalline lagoons scattered like jewels in the desert. 
During the rainy season these lagoons form, creating a contrast between the azure waters and the pristine sand. 
The best time to go is between June and September, as during this time there is usually enough water from the past rainy season.
